SummaryEnglish: Explores anime, manga, and otaku culture with top anime YouTubers Joey from the The Anime Man, Garnt from Gigguk, and Connor from Cdawgva and occasionally special guests.

1.SummaryEnglish: They couldn't find a good chess anime, so they made their own. Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk) and Connor (CDawgVA) talk about their experience competing in the Chess.com Twitch Ani-tuber tournament arc.

2.TitleEnglish: We Tried Real Tokyo Drifting and FAILED
2.SummaryEnglish: The boys go out the studio one of the rare times to try out drifting. They go to Ebisu Circuit to learn how to drift. This special also featured Abroad in Japan, who was the videographer and driver.

3.TitleEnglish: We Tried Cycling Across Japan and FAILED
3.SummaryEnglish: On this special episode of Trash Taste Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk), and Connor (CDawgVA) visit Onomichi in Hiroshima Prefecture to compete in a cycling challenge along the Shimanami Kaido. This route is a 75 km bike ride allowing cycling to island hope the scenic view. Who will come out on top and crown themselves the ultimate cyclist at the finish line?

4.SummaryEnglish: The hosts are each tasked to put together a PC in the fastest time. Thanks again to Gigabyte Aorus for all the PC parts!

6.SummaryEnglish: The hosts travel 3,274 kilometres (2,034 mi) in nine days across Mainland Japan, from Cape Sata to Cape Sōya.

28.SummaryEnglish: Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk) and Connor (CDawgVA) talk about real life friends vs online friends and the lessons they they learned from them. Connor and Garnt celebrate one year living in Japan and reminiscence about their time, what they love, what's become boring, and what they hope to do. Everyone takes a moment to reflect about the cultural world view, were they want to visit and plans for the future if they didn't have YouTube or if YouTube were to disappear in the future

37.SummaryEnglish: On this episode of Trash Taste Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk), and Connor (CDawgVA) talk health, meme stocks, investments, and multi marketing bullshit. Then in a surprise specials Connor fulfills his promise from episode four and presents his power point presentation on "A YouTuber Guide To Being Hit On". The 93% show off their cringy side and the boys have a chance to reflect on relationships and being a YouTuber.

Then they take a trip down memory lane about how their childhood was easier and their trading carding empire. Finally they discuss spoilers and if the their should be a buffer after a show airs, spoilers: not everyone agrees.

40.TitleEnglish: The WORST Japanese Convenience Store Food
40.SummaryEnglish: Some of this food is about to go into straight into the TRASH after the boys TASTE a wide variety of Japanese convenience store food. Can Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk), and Connor (CDawgVA) stomach hold out? What's worth getting and what you should stay away from? All this this and more on this episode of Trash Taste.

41.SummaryEnglish: When you become an internet celebrity you're expected to lose all your privacy... right? Joey (TheAnimeMan), Garnt (Gigguk), and Connor (CDawgVA) talk about their lives as well known online content creators and how important it is to set boundaries to maintain private self.
